               <floruit notBefore="1790" notAfter="1810">He was a prominent late 18th to early 19th century traditional scholar,
                   a native of either <placeName ref="LOC3549Gojjam">Goǧǧām</placeName> or <placeName ref="LOC6569Tegray">Tǝgrāy </placeName>. 
                  He taught in <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar </placeName> 
                  where he was elevated to the rank of <persName ref="PRS5821Kabte">
                     <roleName type="title">ʿaqqābe saʾāt</roleName> 
                  </persName>
                  
                  during the rule of 
                  <persName ref="PRS9153TaklaHa">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Takla Hāymānot II</persName>.
                  He was a highly talented scholar whose brilliance attested in 
                  the book of <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1949Mashaf">Maṣḥafa mǝkr</ref>, 
                  authored by <persName ref="PRS11347TaklaHay">Takla Hāymānot of Mamsāḥ</persName>.</floruit>
               <death notBefore="1784" notAfter="1788">He died during the tenure of 
                  <persName ref="PRS1719AliGwan">
                     <roleName type="title">rās </roleName> ʾAli Gwāngul</persName>. </death>
               
               
